Business Development Officer
- ,
Date Posted: 2014/05/05 10:12:16
Ref. JB3047417
Job Description
Key tasks of the role
Work of the business development officer is primarily focused on Researching, and contacting prospect customers through telephone calls to develop the business of Gael.
The Business Development Officer will perform the following tasks:
• Support Gael business strategy through market data research and cold calling.
• Achieve defined business targets and key performance indicators
• Carrying out sales lead generation campaigns (both telephone and email)
• Update Gael’s Customer Relationship Management system with business development activities and customer communications
• Respond to follow up requests.
• Manage some existing accounts
• Conduct Quarterly Customer calls and site visits
• Understand potential clients’ requirements and align them to company’s products
• Set up trials on products
• Follow up on trials, payment and subscription renewals
• Up-sell products to existing customers
• Provide exemplary customer service/relationship management
• Document all communications
• Update team on accounts and action status in daily/weekly meetings
• Administrative work maybe required
Skills
Skills
What we are looking for?
•	excellent verbal and written communication
•	Strong telephone presence and confidence in making telephone introductions
•	Proven ability to convey complex information in a clear and concise way with excellent telephone manners.
•	Proven ability to communicate effectively at all levels.
•	Excellent written skills.
•	Proven ability to work autonomously and to a deadline
•	 Confident, self-motivated and focused
•	 Flexible with time and travel commitments (overseas travel will be required)
•	 Computer literate (Word, Excel, PowerPoint, CRM and mind mapping, Lotus notes, CRM)
Qualifications
•1-2 years direct sales experience in a high volume outbound sales call role
• Cold calling and prospecting experience
• Fluent in English Verbal & Written
• Arabic speaker is an advantage
• Valid UAE driving license
• Able to travel to ME countries especially – Bahrain, Kuwait, Jordan, Qatar, Saudi Arabia
• Base location will be Dubai, UAE, although travel will be required. Therefore you must be willing to work away from home as and when required.
• Travel to UK may also be required as extensive training will be provided.
•A desire to develop and grow with training and programs
• Able to work in a diverse cultural environment
